Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.61,0:00:04.07,Italics,rep,0000,0000,0000,,This being the first civilian \NAntarctic expedition,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.07,0:00:08.31,Italics,rep,0000,0000,0000,,some are saying that this brings \NAntarctica closer to the average person.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.31,0:00:11.48,Main,taka,0000,0000,0000,,Now that Syowa Station has been \Ntransferred to civilian ownership,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.48,0:00:14.04,Main,taka,0000,0000,0000,,I believe there will be more \Nchances for things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.04,0:00:16.61,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Do you intend to continue \Ndoing research like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.16,0:00:18.24,Main,taka,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.14,0:00:21.49,Main,taka,0000,0000,0000,,Even having become civilians,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.49,0:00:24.22,Main,taka,0000,0000,0000,,we'd like to keep sending expeditions \Nand doing observation...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.46,0:00:33.44,Main,taka,0000,0000,0000,,We want everyone to learn about \Nthe wonders of Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:01:01.20,Show_Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2280,1225)}A Place Further Than the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:23.49,Ep_Title,sign,0000,0000,0000,,The Ship That Sees the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:23.49,sign_3309_12_Duty_Free_Articl,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Duty-Free Articles
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:23.49,sign_3309_13_Duty_Free_Articl,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Duty-Free Articles
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:23.49,Likes/Comments,sign,0000,0000,0000,,15 Likes\N5 Comments
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:23.49,Hashtags,sign,0000,0000,0000,,#Catchy #Witty #Sensational
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.49,0:02:25.20,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Let's run a test.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:26.50,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.50,0:02:29.02,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,We're doing this for you, \Nthough, Shirase-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.02,0:02:31.13,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.13,0:02:32.88,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Jumping!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:37.69,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,And as you can see, we've arrived \Nin Fremantle in a snap!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.69,0:02:38.88,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Please, observe!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.88,0:02:42.14,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This is the expedition ship \Nfrom Japan, the {\i1}Penguin Manju{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.14,0:02:45.94,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ship we're going \Nto take to Antarctica!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.94,0:02:48.90,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's head inside the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.90,0:02:52.15,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Now... take it, Shirase-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.15,0:02:58.40,sign_4128_29_High_School_Girl,sign,0000,0000,0000,,High School Girl\NYuzuki Shiraishi\NChallenge For Antarctic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.04,0:02:55.71,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Right! I am High School Girl \NAntarctic Expedition Member,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.71,0:02:58.40,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kobuchizawa Shirase!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.60,0:03:03.28,Main,sign,0000,0000,0000,,F-From here, I'll b-be making some \Nc-c-catchy, witty, sensational reports
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.56,0:03:07.66,Main,sign,0000,0000,0000,,as I l-lead you all around Antarctica!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.30,0:03:12.16,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.16,0:03:14.62,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I told you I didn't want this stupid thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.62,0:03:17.63,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid thing?! I wrote you a script \Nbecause you said you wanted one!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.63,0:03:19.17,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.56,0:03:21.35,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,it sure is big.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.35,0:03:22.95,Main,yuka,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to go without saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.95,0:03:25.56,Main,yuka,0000,0000,0000,,but it did come all the \Nway from over the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.56,0:03:26.81,Main,yuka,0000,0000,0000,,From Japan...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.88,0:03:30.30,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations on your long journey!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.30,0:03:31.85,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Come on up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.43,0:03:34.58,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Kanae-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.58,0:03:35.23,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:38.36,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,You've finally reached the starting line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.45,0:03:43.58,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of the rooms look the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.58,0:03:45.07,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,so make sure you remember your number.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:46.95,sign_5397_48_Passenger__Passe,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Passenger: Passenger: Passenger: Passenger:\NMiyake      Tamaki      Shiraishi    Kobuchizawa\NHinata       Mari           Yuzuki      Shirase
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:46.95,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,Kanae-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.65,0:03:49.70,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,The packages we just brought on...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.70,0:03:51.82,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be there in a minute. Just wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.21,0:03:53.79,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,A four-person room, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:55.43,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds fun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.05,0:03:57.86,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,There will be fights here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.86,0:03:58.90,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.90,0:04:00.38,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try to be optimistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.84,0:04:01.91,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,But it does seem likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.91,0:04:03.01,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.63,0:04:07.68,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,You have desks and lockers, \Nso figure out who'll go where.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:10.56,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,And those are the belongings \Nyou had sent from Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.52,0:04:13.40,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Don't open them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.40,0:04:15.65,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be carrying them to \Nthe station after we arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.65,0:04:16.44,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.78,0:04:17.68,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.16,0:04:19.65,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,They're locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.65,0:04:22.16,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,So they don't open by themselves \Nwhen the boat sways...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:24.22,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Vice commander!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.73,0:04:27.32,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,The welcome party will \Nbe soon, so until then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.32,0:04:28.98,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,Kanae-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.98,0:04:30.95,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.16,0:04:33.91,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,But what should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:36.03,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, there's also a rule: \NDon't step on the silver part here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.03,0:04:36.98,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Just to warn you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.98,0:04:39.16,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,we're going to treat you like \Nadults from now on, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.16,0:04:40.84,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Figure things out for yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:48.39,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,You know, if they see you like \Nthat, they're gonna kick you off.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:52.10,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to sway a lot when \Nthe boat starts moving, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.35,0:04:55.78,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should do the boat \Nreport now, while we still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:04:56.84,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.40,0:04:59.43,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Which way did we come from again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.65,0:05:05.00,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,There was a map in the brochure, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.62,0:05:06.53,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.74,0:05:10.40,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,And so we open this, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.04,0:05:13.65,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,We're outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.95,0:05:18.86,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,We are up quite high...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.08,0:05:22.38,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Yuzuki-chan, are you acrophobic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.38,0:05:23.32,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,For real?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.32,0:05:24.88,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Why does that make you so happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.20,0:05:26.88,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let's go up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:28.69,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.69,0:05:29.76,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I would like to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.29,0:05:32.06,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go this way. This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.01,0:05:36.06,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,It's the snow cat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.55,0:05:39.81,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! So they store it in there, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.14,0:05:43.19,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, we definitely gotta cover this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.19,0:05:44.15,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Shirase!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.17,0:05:46.37,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a script?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.37,0:05:49.45,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Ad-libbing is a reporter's responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:51.06,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Filming now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.32,0:05:52.33,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:05:54.78,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,It's so old. Is it really going to move?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.78,0:05:58.07,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,They said it would be fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.48,0:06:01.81,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,I have a feeling we don't have \Nenough people down below, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:04.42,sign_8630_106_Do_your_best__,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Do your best!!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.92,0:06:04.42,sign_8630_104_Civilian_Antarct,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Civilian Antarctic\NExpedition Members!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.81,0:06:03.55,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should go help them later.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:04.42,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.60,0:06:06.43,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,No rest for the wicked...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.05,0:06:10.89,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:13.33,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,W-We're on the expedition ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.32,0:06:17.65,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,And... there's a snow cat over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.27,0:06:20.91,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ship's bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.91,0:06:24.69,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't left yet, so they \Nlet us stop by to visit!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.69,0:06:27.56,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This is the ship's captain, Mukai-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.56,0:06:31.28,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,And the expedition's commander, Todo-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.28,0:06:36.75,sign_9382_117_Worthless,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Worthless
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.74,0:06:34.73,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first civilian \Nexpedition in three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.73,0:06:36.75,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Could you tell us what \Nyour goal is this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.53,0:06:40.04,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,We have several.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:45.68,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,Syowa Station has been unmanned \Nsince the winter team pulled out,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.68,0:06:50.41,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,so restoring it to normal functionality \Nis our primary motivation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.11,0:06:47.13,Main,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.54,0:06:53.18,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.67,0:06:58.60,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be visiting that same \NSyowa Station very soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.60,0:06:59.94,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,See you then!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.79,0:07:02.27,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you do what she does?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.30,0:07:03.09,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:03.69,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,There's a reason she's a pro!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.16,0:07:05.74,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Do you like the ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.74,0:07:08.21,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! It's so big!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.21,0:07:09.14,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.14,0:07:10.07,Main,muka,0000,0000,0000,,I gotta say...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.53,0:07:14.41,Main,muka,0000,0000,0000,,I think this ship might be \Na little too big this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.92,0:07:17.01,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,Captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.96,0:07:19.39,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,Have you been to your room yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.39,0:07:20.29,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.83,0:07:23.01,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.01,0:07:26.17,Main,todo,0000,0000,0000,,That's the same room Takako used.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.54,0:07:30.90,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Find anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.90,0:07:32.76,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,No. Not even a doodle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.92,0:07:35.09,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing in here, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.49,0:07:37.81,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, even though it's the same room,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.81,0:07:40.51,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,they might have changed all the equipment...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.51,0:07:41.27,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,True...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:42.60,Main,yumi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.40,0:07:44.81,Main,yumi,0000,0000,0000,,Yumiko-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:49.03,Main,yumi,0000,0000,0000,,I know you just got here, but do \Nyou have a little time to help out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:50.94,Main,yumi,0000,0000,0000,,We're so short-handed...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.94,0:07:53.53,sign_11292_149_When_you_re_out_,sign,0000,0000,0000,,When you're out, turn your card to red
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.24,0:07:58.62,Main,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Then there's eggs, milk, yogurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.62,0:07:59.47,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,What about pudding?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.47,0:08:00.46,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:05.35,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,But eggs and milk... are those \Nprovisions for the boat trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.35,0:08:07.42,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.42,0:08:08.74,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.74,0:08:09.70,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.70,0:08:12.09,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I just find it a little weird \Nthey're going shopping now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.37,0:08:13.64,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.64,0:08:15.95,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I had this image of them dropping
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.95,0:08:19.52,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,this many-ton crate of \Nprovisions onto the ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.35,0:08:23.18,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Are you with an expedition?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.18,0:08:24.45,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.45,0:08:25.94,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,You're so young.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.94,0:08:28.52,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,To think even girls like you are \Nallowed to head out these days...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.52,0:08:29.76,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,All this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.76,0:08:31.53,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't that much, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:36.03,Main,man,0000,0000,0000,,The new ship that came by last \Nweek had a whole container full.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.41,0:08:42.29,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,So heavy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.34,0:08:45.54,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:48.04,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,There are quite a few...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.04,0:08:49.41,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,"Not enough funds."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.41,0:08:50.50,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,"Not enough people."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.84,0:08:52.51,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,"The plan itself is unworkable."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.02,0:08:56.07,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,"There's a new station and \Nexpedition ship anyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.07,0:08:57.70,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,so doubling up is meaningless."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.70,0:08:58.75,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds about right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.75,0:09:02.06,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm turning it off. I don't have \Nmuch room on this disposable SIM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.38,0:09:04.52,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Shirase-chan, do you know anything about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:07.82,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I never even thought about that \Nwhen we were coming here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.82,0:09:09.60,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, guess you wouldn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.60,0:09:10.52,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Still...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.91,0:09:14.11,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like things are a \Nbit strange on board, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.66,0:09:16.95,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,There don't appear to be enough people,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.95,0:09:19.24,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,and there seem to be a \Nlot of problems, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.12,0:09:21.08,Main,woman,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.64,0:09:23.45,Main,woman,0000,0000,0000,,How did your first errand go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.73,0:09:26.46,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Good! This is enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.23,0:09:28.96,Main,woman,0000,0000,0000,,Great job, great job.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.96,0:09:31.80,Main,woman,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm sure the locals are \Nused to this song and dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.89,0:09:34.47,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,They did seem to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.79,0:09:36.81,Main,woman,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.23,0:09:44.63,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Um... could we ask an awkward question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.14,0:09:47.93,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Can we really get to Antarctica?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.93,0:09:48.52,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.25,0:09:50.65,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.08,0:09:53.29,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,After all, Antarctica's not going anywhe—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.29,0:09:54.80,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Please, spare us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.53,0:10:03.30,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't know where you heard about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.30,0:10:05.50,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,but I understand the nerves.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.90,0:10:08.39,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We have so few people and supplies...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.39,0:10:11.46,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Since we're civilians, \Nwe've had to make lots of cuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:12.80,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,So it's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.80,0:10:13.80,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.91,0:10:18.34,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,as I said before, \Nthere's no way we're not going.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.69,0:10:20.84,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We've made all the necessary preparations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:22.85,sign_14886_207_First_Civilian_A,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Fi{\c&H50B1DF&}rs{\c&H46F0DF&}t C{\c&H44EDC9&}iv{\c&H3FF780&}il{\c&H7DEE40&}ia{\c&HC6E145&}n\NA{\c&HD0A447&}ntar{\c&HCF3A35&}ctic {\c&HCD2E77&}Expe{\c&HBB2EA4&}dit{\c&H882FA7&}ion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.84,0:10:24.61,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,And we've taken unprecedented \Nprecautions with safety, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:26.73,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,And most importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.17,0:10:32.84,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,the people on this ship are determined to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.29,0:10:36.48,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Determined...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.30,0:10:40.32,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Antarctica is an unforgiving place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.42,0:10:45.06,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Blizzards blow at minus dozens of degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.06,0:10:49.02,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,The air is so dry that \Nyour lips chap and bleed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.39,0:10:54.09,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,The sunlight is harsh, so if you forget \Nsunblock, you can really get burned.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.09,0:10:56.78,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,There's no Internet, \Nand no places to have fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.71,0:10:59.42,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, we're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:02.96,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Preparing little by little \Nover three years' time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.42,0:11:05.22,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.48,0:11:06.92,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.46,0:11:09.10,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,If I had to put it into words...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.61,0:11:14.28,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,This time, it's to see the sky, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.03,0:11:15.73,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,The sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.84,0:11:17.46,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.49,0:11:19.50,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,The sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.21,0:11:29.51,Main,mari,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.00,0:11:31.42,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.42,0:11:35.27,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,She sounded honest, but also \Nlike she was hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.27,0:11:37.03,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,She was absolutely hiding something!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.03,0:11:38.09,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.34,0:11:41.38,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,She said it herself! They're "determined"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.38,0:11:43.84,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,They must have a serious reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.84,0:11:46.35,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,The sky, huh? I wonder what that meant!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.35,0:11:47.95,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,No way to find out, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.95,0:11:50.61,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. No matter how we try to press it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.61,0:11:52.52,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,when an adult says something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.60,0:11:55.36,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,We must investigate!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.26,0:11:57.67,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Which way do we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.56,0:12:01.99,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Good thing we're all on the same page.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:05.99,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.99,0:12:08.99,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who told me to go, Yu-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.21,0:12:12.17,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,Why? Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.17,0:12:13.79,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I do want to go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.79,0:12:16.51,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,You know I want to see you, Yu-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.51,0:12:20.63,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even know if this \Nexpedition is gonna work out...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.63,0:12:22.26,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you, I love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.26,0:12:24.76,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,I've told you I love you so many times!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.69,0:12:24.46,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Nobue-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.46,0:12:26.01,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,We're going out for a drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.58,0:12:29.26,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, why does it have to be like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.58,0:12:29.26,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.46,0:12:32.08,Main,nobu,0000,0000,0000,,Is the fact that I love you not enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.63,0:12:36.65,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, only two days \Nleft for short sleeves...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.65,0:12:38.31,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.31,0:12:40.25,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have a Kahlua!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.25,0:12:41.90,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if they have cocktails...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:44.07,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,So, what did you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.07,0:12:45.64,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I was thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.64,0:12:49.24,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,I think the project itself \Nmight not be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.54,0:12:51.95,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,That's your personal opinion, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.51,0:12:56.03,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,The actual details haven't \Neven been decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.03,0:12:58.54,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,There's not really anything we can say yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.54,0:13:01.24,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Yume-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.24,0:13:03.17,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,You're already sloshed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.17,0:13:04.47,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,Gonna carry her back?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.47,0:13:05.79,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Hell no!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.79,0:13:09.24,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,All of us crammed in together, \NI'd never hear the end of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.24,0:13:10.85,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get back to the plan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.10,0:13:12.06,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,Concretely speaking,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.06,0:13:16.76,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,what we're doing right now isn't \Npart of the official plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.76,0:13:19.85,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, that's an \Nextremely distant goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.85,0:13:23.46,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,But the commander and Kanae-san \Nare obsessed with it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.46,0:13:25.33,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,That's incorrect.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.24,0:13:28.43,Main,yume,0000,0000,0000,,The other members are obsessed with it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.43,0:13:29.35,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,That makes it even more—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.35,0:13:32.66,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,You sayin' you're 'gainst it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.66,0:13:34.56,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it. I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.56,0:13:37.67,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,A real man wouldn't grumble 'bout everythin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:38.63,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:41.49,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.49,0:13:44.17,Main,hona,0000,0000,0000,,High school girls in masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.77,0:13:47.16,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.03,0:13:50.80,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I told you! I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.80,0:13:52.02,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to say it twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:55.68,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,They have some amazing plan \Nthey haven't told anyone about!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.23,0:13:57.94,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,But what could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.59,0:13:59.86,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,You think...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.09,0:14:06.97,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Antarctic People!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.37,0:14:09.40,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Nice one!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.40,0:14:10.33,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect timing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.33,0:14:12.03,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Please, take this seriously!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.37,0:14:15.26,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,What if they're planning something awful?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:18.17,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,They could force us to go along with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.41,0:14:21.97,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,But thinking won't get us anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.97,0:14:23.89,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Even so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.89,0:14:26.90,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to talk to Kanae-san \None more time tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:29.05,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Shirase-chan, that's my plushy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.22,0:14:33.44,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.85,0:14:37.95,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Glow-in-the-dark paint!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.42,0:14:39.44,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Shirase.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.71,0:14:40.68,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna sleep here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.71,0:14:48.83,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,You think Shirase-chan's mother did that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.83,0:14:50.20,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.20,0:14:53.95,Flashback_Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,If I had to put it into words...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.21,0:14:57.33,Flashback_Italics,kana,0000,0000,0000,,This time, it's to see the sky, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.64,0:15:08.58,Italics,shira,0000,0000,0000,,A place more distant than the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.42,0:15:13.59,Italics,shira,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a prison, a place trapped in ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.50,0:15:17.73,Italics,shira,0000,0000,0000,,It's a place, still unopened,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:20.06,Italics,shira,0000,0000,0000,,yet filled with possibilities,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.59,0:15:22.78,Italics,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Earth's greatest treasure chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.74,0:15:34.09,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Want to look?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.16,0:15:42.23,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I think we all got a little \Ntoo worked up to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.13,0:15:44.29,Flashback,gin,0000,0000,0000,,As civilians?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.29,0:15:47.00,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! After the new ship is finished,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.00,0:15:49.43,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,they'll be deployed to the new station,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.43,0:15:52.39,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,and the current ship and Syowa Station
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.39,0:15:54.46,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,will be transferred to civilian ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.46,0:15:55.55,Flashback,taka,0000,0000,0000,,You mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.55,0:15:58.43,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We can become the first civilian team—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.43,0:15:58.98,Flashback,taka,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.98,0:16:00.18,Flashback,both,0000,0000,0000,,That was fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.93,0:16:03.19,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,The ship and the station \Nwere both hand-me-downs,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.55,0:16:05.34,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,but we were so excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.91,0:16:09.59,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,There are almost no civilian \Nstations anywhere in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.59,0:16:13.49,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,so we came up with all kinds of plans, \Ngathered all kinds of researchers...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.44,0:16:17.63,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,We all wanted to make it a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.37,0:16:22.94,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Because we knew that this journey, \Nthis road that we paved,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:25.68,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,would continue on into the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.72,0:16:27.60,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:29.58,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,An astronomical observatory?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.58,0:16:32.46,Flashback,gin,0000,0000,0000,,The plan's been out there for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.46,0:16:35.51,Flashback,gin,0000,0000,0000,,I'd heard they were building \None at the new station, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.51,0:16:37.18,Flashback,taka,0000,0000,0000,,That's all the more reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.77,0:16:40.31,Flashback,taka,0000,0000,0000,,We might not be able to rival \Ntheir scale and amenities,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.79,0:16:43.57,Flashback,taka,0000,0000,0000,,but I think being able to do the \Nsame research as the new station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.57,0:16:47.27,Flashback,taka,0000,0000,0000,,is the most important thing we can \Ndo as civilians in the future!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.50,0:16:50.51,Flashback,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.51,0:16:52.58,Flashback,kana,0000,0000,0000,,As good publicity, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.82,0:17:02.79,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,She was probably hoping to find \Nsomething worthwhile somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.50,0:17:08.29,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Even though she knew that feeling \Ncould be very dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.66,0:17:09.80,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Somewhere out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.08,0:17:11.51,Flashback,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Takako!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.28,0:17:18.92,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,When we came home, we found a \Nharsh reality waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.89,0:17:24.47,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Sponsors, afraid of the damage \Nto their image, withdrew one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.47,0:17:26.80,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,And the next expedition was \Nindefinitely postponed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.23,0:17:29.40,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,and the winter mission was withdrawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.82,0:17:31.19,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.19,0:17:34.78,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,But we hadn't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.38,0:17:38.14,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Three years ago, in the place \Nwe discovered with Takako...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.14,0:17:42.54,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,with your mother, we would some \Nday look at the stars again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.76,0:17:46.79,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't matter if it \Ntook ten years or twenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:48.79,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,And it wasn't just us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.00,0:17:53.30,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the members who were with us \Nthree years ago are here again now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:57.96,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Our budget has been mostly stripped away, \Nand we'll get almost no compensation,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.96,0:18:01.12,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,and there are some of us who won't have \Nanything waiting for us when we return.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.29,0:18:03.67,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,And yet we all came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.35,0:18:05.81,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,And yet we're all still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.00,0:18:10.31,Main,gin,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of ship this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.59,0:18:17.95,Italics,taka,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Gin. Want to go to Antarctica?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:19.95,Italics,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Antarctica?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.30,0:18:21.54,Italics,gin,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.54,0:18:22.71,Italics,taka,0000,0000,0000,,You know, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.74,0:18:24.86,Italics,taka,0000,0000,0000,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.94,0:18:29.97,Italics,taka,0000,0000,0000,,love leaving my footprints in fresh snow!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.20,0:18:38.22,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's been a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.22,0:18:40.22,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Maekawa Kanae!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:41.72,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,How is everyone doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.96,0:18:45.94,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.34,0:18:49.41,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Now, it's been three years \Nsince the last voyage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:52.40,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you've all been through a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.40,0:18:55.90,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Some of you have lost hair, \Nsome have gotten divorced,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.90,0:18:57.76,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,some have lost your jobs...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:18:59.91,Main,yumi,0000,0000,0000,,No one got married?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.09,0:19:03.43,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's all introduce \Nourselves one by one!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.88,0:19:05.16,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,But first...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.37,0:19:08.17,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,what you've all been waiting for, \Nlet's introduce our passengers!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.69,0:19:09.83,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.30,0:19:16.52,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Don't look at the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.52,0:19:17.26,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.26,0:19:19.05,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,They're in high school!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.29,0:19:21.16,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,They're not Goto or Yajima in drag!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.16,0:19:24.13,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,They're real high school girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.21,0:19:27.48,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Now, a warning they're not legal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.48,0:19:29.73,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say it one more time. They're not legal.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.73,0:19:31.10,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,Toshio, you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.10,0:19:33.11,Main,shi,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you single me out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.68,0:19:44.87,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,All of our members who made that promise\Nthree years ago have returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.23,0:19:49.52,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,And with our new members, all of us here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.52,0:19:52.03,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,these members, are going to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.80,0:19:54.36,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to Antarctica!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.88,0:20:12.90,Main,kana,0000,0000,0000,,All right! From right to left, \Nlet's have some introductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.14,0:20:17.01,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Tamaki Mari. Please call me Kimari!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.01,0:20:20.35,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I wanted to go somewhere new,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:22.91,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,to make a real change in my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.18,0:20:26.12,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,And the next thing I knew, \NI was heading for Antarctica.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.12,0:20:30.20,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any idea what I am doing, \Nbut I look forward to working with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.42,0:20:32.42,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,Shiraishi Yuzuki here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.42,0:20:35.94,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a year younger than the others here, \Nin my first year in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.94,0:20:39.49,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up on this boat for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.49,0:20:41.73,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,The truth is, I really didn't want to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.69,0:20:46.52,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,but I came here wanting to do \Nsomething with other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.52,0:20:47.97,Main,yuzu,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to working with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.97,0:20:49.84,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,Miyake Hinata here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.84,0:20:52.03,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I'm cheerful and energetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:55.14,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I came here because I \Nwanted to do something big
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.14,0:20:57.98,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,before I took my entrance exams.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.98,0:21:01.83,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I might be little, but I've got a big heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.83,0:21:03.49,Main,hina,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to working with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.12,0:21:08.03,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... Kobuchizawa Shirase.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.72,0:21:12.12,Main,kima,0000,0000,0000,,Shirase-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.36,0:21:33.65,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I boarded this ship to do catchy, \Nwitty, sensational reporting!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.07,0:21:36.73,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,I want to open the treasure \Nchest of Antarctica
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.73,0:21:38.94,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,that my mother wrote about with my own hands!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.44,0:21:44.47,Main,shira,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, let's go to Antarctica together!
